<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-03T07:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-03T07:35:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1866: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-03T16:00:00+03:25">May 3,
                                    1942—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 3—9:53 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>139. My number 134. Kuniholm reports as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>May 2, 2 p.m. Soviet Consul General, commanding officer Red
                                    troops, Iranian officials, and Kurds have met at Askerabad
                                    village near Rezaieh. Kurds have resented [<hi rend="italic">presented</hi>] series of demands which must be discussed
                                    further at Tehran as well as by Russians. Soviet Consul General
                                    has appealed to Kurds to disband and go home. Kurdish
                                    depredations continue.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>